  <!-- Risk callouts -->
  <div class="pl-callout pl-callout-risk">
    <div class="pl-callout-title">R1 (HIGH) — Real SSE cadence may split NDJSON lines</div>
    OpenRouter chunk boundaries may arrive mid-JSON-line. A naive per-chunk JSON.parse will silently drop sections. The line-buffer accumulator is mandatory; unit-tested with split-chunk fixtures. Schedule the real-transport integration test (wrangler dev + real stream) as step 1 of implementation.
  </div>

  <div class="pl-callout pl-callout-warn">
    <div class="pl-callout-title">R2 (MED) — Model NDJSON compliance is not guaranteed</div>
    claude-3.5-haiku may emit markdown fences or prose between NDJSON lines. The parser must skip non-JSON lines gracefully. Manual smoke with the real model required before sign-off.
  </div>

  <div class="pl-callout pl-callout-info">
    <div class="pl-callout-title">R3 (MED) — D1 write-per-section adds resume lag</div>
    Fire-and-forget D1 writes mean the resume position may lag 1 section behind the client state. Acceptable — the client already has the section in React state; the lag is only visible on hard reconnect.
  </div>

